yright\par \tab \loch\af4\dbch\af4\hich\f4 \u-3\'f0\loch\f4 I\tab insert work space\par \tab \loch\af4\dbch\af4\hich\f4 \u-3\'f0\loch\f4 O\tab delete line to default buffer\par \tab \loch\af4\dbch\af4\hich\f4 \u-3\'f0\loch\f4 P\tab insert line from default buffer\par \tab \loch\af4\dbch\af4\hich\f4 \u-3\'f0\loch\f4 S\tab create subroutine header\par \tab \loch\af4\dbch\af4\hich\f4 \u-3\'f0\loch\f4 T\tab inser\hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 t space in header\par \par }\pard\plain \s1\keepn\widctlpar\outlinelevel0\adjustright \b\fs36\kerning28\loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\f4\cgrid {\hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 If You Have Problems\par }\pard\plain \qj\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\f4\cgrid {\par \hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 A program comment form is included here for any comments you may have about ORCA.  We welcome any form of comment, be it constructive criticism, something you especially liked about ORCA, bug reports or documentatio\hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 n errors.\par \par \hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 If you are reporting a suspected bug, please be very specific.  We received one letter for DOS ORCA which said, "when you fix the bug in the directive, please let me know."  We didn't know there was a bug, and had used the directive successfully\hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4  ourselves.  And of course the writer didn't even hint at what sort of problem he had had.  We still don't even know if it was a bug or a user error!  In any case, when you report a bug, you must supply us with enough information for us to see the bug.  U\hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 n\hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 til we see the problem, we really can't work on it.  And, of course, be sure and tell us what hardware you have on your Apple.  We aren't being nosy - we have seen several very peculiar bugs in software caused by a completely illogical conflict with a pie\hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 c\hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 e of hardware.\par \par \hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 If you are having difficulty using ORCA, you can also call or write for support.  Please understand that this support must be limited to answering specific questions.  We cannot get involved in debugging your software.\par \par \hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 You can contact us a\hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 t:\par \par \tab \hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 The Byte Works, Inc.\par \tab \hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 4700 Irving Blvd N.W., Suite 207\par \tab \hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 Albuquerque, New Mexico  87114\par \par \tab \hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 Phone: (505) 898-8183\par \par \par }}